2. AutoPET-3 LesionTracer (MIC-DKFZ/autopet-3-submission)
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Copyright: Division of Medical Image Computing, German Cancer Research Center (DKFZ)
   URL: https://github.com/MIC-DKFZ/autopet-3-submission
   Usage: Whole-body PET/CT lesion segmentation model

3. TotalSegmentator (wasserth/TotalSegmentator)
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Copyright: Jakob Wasserthal
   URL: https://github.com/wasserth/TotalSegmentator
   Note: Some specialized task models (e.g., brain_aneurysm) may use CC BY-NC 4.0.
         The default "total" task used by DICOMclaw is Apache 2.0.
   Usage: Organ segmentation from CT volumes

4. Cornerstone3D (cornerstonejs/cornerstone3D)
   License: MIT License
   Copyright: Open Health Imaging Foundation
   URL: https://github.com/cornerstonejs/cornerstone3D
   Usage: DICOM image rendering and viewport management in the web viewer

